                    },
                    "content": {
                        "content_type": "text",
                        "parts": [
                            "A TypeError when passing arguments typically occurs when you pass the wrong number or type of arguments. Here are some common causes:\n\n1. **Missing required arguments**: Make sure you're passing all required parameters.\n2. **Wrong argument types**: Check if the function expects specific types.\n3. **Positional vs keyword arguments**: Ensure you're using the correct argument format.\n\nExample fix:\n```python\ndef greet(name, age):\n    return f'Hello {name}, you are {age} years old'\n\n# Wrong: greet('Alice')  # Missing 'age' argument\n# Correct:\ngreet('Alice', 25)\n```"
                        ]
                    },
