                    "content": {
                        "content_type": "text",
                        "parts": [
                            "Great question! Here's a breakdown:\n\n## Supervised Learning\n- Uses **labeled data** for training\n- Algorithm learns to map inputs to known outputs\n- Examples: Classification, Regression\n- Use cases: Spam detection, price prediction\n\n## Unsupervised Learning\n- Uses **unlabeled data**\n- Algorithm finds patterns and structures in data\n- Examples: Clustering, Dimensionality Reduction\n- Use cases: Customer segmentation, anomaly detection\n\nThe key difference is whether you have ground truth labels to guide the learning process."
                        ]
                    },
